members.name: DocumentTimeline()
members.description: Creates a new DocumentTimeline object associated with the active document of the current browsing context.

parameters.name: options
parameters.description: An object specifying options for the new timeline. Currently the only supported option is the originTime member which specifies the zero time for the documentTimeline as a real number of milliseconds relative to the navigationStart moment of the active document for the current browsing context.

members.name: AnimationTimeline.currentTime
members.description: Returns the time value in milliseconds for this timeline or null if it is inactive.
